<hl>
<seg id=1> Fei Xiaotong was awarded the Marcos Prize. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Manila, 31 August, by Xong Changyi Dr Fei Xiaotong, a famous Chinese sociologist, Vice Chief Committee Member of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, was awarded "the Social Leadership" of the 1994 Marcos Prize today. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The Medal-Awarding Ceremony took place in the Cultural Center of the Philippines. </seg>
<seg id=4> President of the Philippines Marcos attended the ceremony and awarded the medals, bonuses and certificates to the 6 chosen outstanding persons this year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> In his speech to express appreciation, Fei Xiaotong said: "I will certainly live up to the encouragement of my friendly neighbors. No matter how much time has left for me, I must make use of my time carefully to do something beneficial for the Asian people as well as the whole world. Let people's knowledge push the society forward to a better future". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The prize named after the former President of the Philippines Ferdinand Marcos was considered to be the Asian Nobel Prize. </seg>
<seg id=7> The annual prize consists of five items awarded to the outstanding persons and organizations of government offices, public services, social leadership, journalism, creation and communication of literature and arts as well as international negotiation, etc. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Since it was founded in 1958, 172 individuals and 14 organizations have been awarded the prize. </seg>
</p>
